---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Git Cheatsheet ‚Äî AI Basics">
  <div class="page">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="header">
      <div class="header-left">
        <div class="series-tag">AI Basics ‚Äî Issue 02</div>
        <h1>Git<br><em>Cheatsheet</em></h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Everything you need. Nothing you don't.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="header-right">
        <div class="big-label">Lost In AI Land</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Core Commands -->
    <div class="section-title">Essential Git Commands</div>
    <div class="col-labels">
      <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ command</div>
      <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ what it does</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
      <div class="card-body">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="raw"><span class="cmd">git init</span></div>
          <div class="rendered">Start tracking a folder as a Git repository</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="raw"><span class="cmd">git add</span> <span class="val">filename</span></div>
          <div class="rendered">Stage a file ‚Äî mark it as ready to save</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="raw"><span class="cmd">git commit -m</span> <span class="val">"message"</span></div>
          <div class="rendered">Take a permanent snapshot with a description</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="raw"><span class="cmd">git status</span></div>
          <div class="rendered">See what's changed since your last commit</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="raw"><span class="cmd">git log</span></div>
          <div class="rendered">View your project's full commit history</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="raw"><span class="cmd">git diff</span></div>
          <div class="rendered">See exactly what changed line-by-line</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Branching + Merging -->
    <div class="grid">
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Branching</div>
        <div class="col-labels">
          <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ command</div>
          <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ what it does</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="raw"><span class="cmd">git branch</span> <span class="val">name</span></div>
              <div class="rendered">Create a new branch</div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="raw"><span class="cmd">git checkout</span> <span class="val">name</span></div>
              <div class="rendered">Switch to that branch</div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="raw"><span class="cmd">git branch -d</span> <span class="val">name</span></div>
              <div class="rendered">Delete a branch</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Merging</div>
        <div class="col-labels">
          <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ command</div>
          <div class="col-label">‚Ü≥ what it does</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="raw"><span class="cmd">git merge</span> <span class="val">branch</span></div>
              <div class="rendered">Combine branch into current</div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="raw"><span class="cmd">git merge --abort</span></div>
              <div class="rendered">Cancel a merge gone wrong</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Commit Metadata -->
    <div class="section-title" style="margin-top: 8px;">The Hidden Layer ‚Äî Commit Metadata</div>
    <div class="commit-card">
      <div class="commit-header">
        <span>example commit</span>
        <span>every commit carries this data</span>
      </div>
      <div class="commit-body">
        <div><span class="commit-hash">commit a3f82bc</span></div>
        <div><span class="commit-key">Author:</span> <span class="commit-val">Josh &lt;josh@example.com&gt;</span></div>
        <div><span class="commit-key">Date:</span> <span class="commit-val">Mon Feb 14 09:22:11 2026 -0500</span></div>
        <div style="margin-top:12px;">Add retry logic for failed API calls</div>
        <div style="margin-top:8px;font-size:12px;color:#b0a898;">- Added exponential backoff on 429 responses</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:#b0a898;">- Updated tests to cover timeout scenarios</div>
      </div>
      <div class="commit-explanation">
        <div class="commit-item">
          <strong>Author + Date</strong>
          <p>Who made the change and when. No guessing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="commit-item">
          <strong>Commit hash</strong>
          <p>Unique ID. Reference any point in history by its hash.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="commit-item">
          <strong>Message</strong>
          <p>Why the change was made. Future you will thank present you.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="commit-item">
          <strong>Why it matters</strong>
          <p>This metadata makes Git auditable ‚Äî exactly what AI agents need to be trustworthy.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Best Practices -->
    <div class="section-title">Best Practices</div>
    <div class="bp-grid">
      <div class="bp-item">
        <div class="bp-icon do">‚úÖ</div>
        <div class="bp-text">
          <strong>Commit early, commit often</strong>
          <p>Small, frequent commits are easier to understand and undo than giant omnibus changes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bp-item">
        <div class="bp-icon dont">‚ùå</div>
        <div class="bp-text">
          <strong>Don't commit secrets or credentials</strong>
          <p>Once in Git history, they're permanent. Use .gitignore to exclude sensitive files.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bp-item">
        <div class="bp-icon do">‚úÖ</div>
        <div class="bp-text">
          <strong>Write clear commit messages</strong>
          <p>Present tense, imperative mood: "Add feature" not "Added feature". Future you needs context.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bp-item">
        <div class="bp-icon dont">‚ùå</div>
        <div class="bp-text">
          <strong>Don't rewrite published history</strong>
          <p>Once you've pushed commits, rewriting them breaks collaboration. Edit locally only.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bp-item">
        <div class="bp-icon do">‚úÖ</div>
        <div class="bp-text">
          <strong>Use branches for new features</strong>
          <p>Keep main stable. Experiment on branches. Merge when ready.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bp-item">
        <div class="bp-icon dont">‚ùå</div>
        <div class="bp-text">
          <strong>Don't skip git status before committing</strong>
          <p>Always check what you're about to commit. Surprises are bad in version control.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- AI Callout -->
    <div class="ai-callout">
      <div class="ai-icon">ü§ñ</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Why AI Agents Live Inside Git</h3>
        <p><strong>Git turns AI decisions into auditable history.</strong> When an AI agent modifies code, every change gets tracked, timestamped, and attributed. You can see exactly what the agent committed, in what order, and roll back with one command.</p>
        <p>Without Git, an AI that modifies your codebase is a black box. With Git, it's a paper trail. <strong>Developers are feeding Git history directly into AI prompts</strong> ‚Äî pasting commit logs and diffs so the model understands what changed and what the previous state was.</p>
        <p><strong>Small, well-described commits aren't just good hygiene anymore.</strong> They're the interface between humans and AI agents trying to understand what the codebase is doing and why.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <div class="footer">
      <div class="footer-left">Lost In AI Land</div>
      <div class="footer-right">AI Basics ¬∑ Issue 02 ¬∑ Git</div>
    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
